			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1780693999371,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "WHAT CHANGES AT EACH HOP  vs  WHAT STAYS THE SAME",
			"rawText": "WHAT CHANGES AT EACH HOP  vs  WHAT STAYS THE SAME",
			"fontSize": 24,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "center",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "WHAT CHANGES AT EACH HOP  vs  WHAT STAYS THE SAME",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.25,
			"hasTextLink": false
		},
		{
			"id": "l1bwAAYK",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -445,
			"y": -1116,
			"width": 1051.97900390625,
			"height": 175,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1a1a1a",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 2,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "f0LYTMJ",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 7936406,
			"version": 112,
			"versionNonce": 1669447960,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1780695938328,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "CHANGES at each router hop:                               NEVER changes end-to-end:\n  -> Source MAC (becomes router outgoing interface MAC)      -> Source IP  (192.168.1.10 - original sender)\n  -> Destination MAC (becomes next-hop device MAC)          -> Destination IP  (10.0.0.20 - final receiver)\n  -> TTL (decremented by 1)                                 -> Data payload  (TCP/UDP content)\n  -> FCS (recalculated for new frame)\n\nMAC addresses are LOCAL, so only valid within a single network segment (between two L2 devices)",
			"rawText": "CHANGES at each router hop:                               NEVER changes end-to-end:\n  -> Source MAC (becomes router outgoing interface MAC)      -> Source IP  (192.168.1.10 - original sender)\n  -> Destination MAC (becomes next-hop device MAC)          -> Destination IP  (10.0.0.20 - final receiver)\n  -> TTL (decremented by 1)                                 -> Data payload  (TCP/UDP content)\n  -> FCS (recalculated for new frame)\n\nMAC addresses are LOCAL, so only valid within a single network segment (between two L2 devices)",
			"fontSize": 20,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "CHANGES at each router hop:                               NEVER changes end-to-end:\n  -> Source MAC (becomes router outgoing interface MAC)      -> Source IP  (192.168.1.10 - original sender)\n  -> Destination MAC (becomes next-hop device MAC)          -> Destination IP  (10.0.0.20 - final receiver)\n  -> TTL (decremented by 1)                                 -> Data payload  (TCP/UDP content)\n  -> FCS (recalculated for new frame)\n\nMAC addresses are LOCAL, so only valid within a single network segment (between two L2 devices)",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.25,
			"hasTextLink": false,
			"link": null
		},
