			"hasTextLink": false
		},
		{
			"id": "PJzkRgEp",
			"type": "text",
			"x": -475,
			"y": -360,
			"width": 593.577392578125,
			"height": 338.0709775468331,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1a1a1a",
			"backgroundColor": "transparent",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 2,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 0,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "f0LYTMV",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 952521,
			"version": 154,
			"versionNonce": 1515441256,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1780696018710,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "ICMP rides inside IP packets (Protocol field = 1).\nUsed for diagnostic and control messages -- NOT for user data.\n\nPING  (ICMP Echo Request / Echo Reply):\n  Send Echo Request to target IP -> receive Echo Reply\n  Measures round-trip time (RTT) and reachability\n  ping 8.8.8.8 -- tests connectivity to Google DNS\n\nTRACEROUTE  (ICMP TTL Exceeded):\n  Sends packets with TTL=1, 2, 3...\n  Each router decrements TTL -> drops at 0 -> sends ICMP TTL Exceeded\n  Builds path map: hop 1 = first router, hop 2 = next router...\n  traceroute 8.8.8.8 reveals entire path to destination\n\nCommon ICMP messages:\n  Type 0  = Echo Reply  |  Type 8  = Echo Request\n  Type 3  = Destination Unreachable  |  Type 11 = TTL Exceeded",
			"rawText": "ICMP rides inside IP packets (Protocol field = 1).\nUsed for diagnostic and control messages -- NOT for user data.\n\nPING  (ICMP Echo Request / Echo Reply):\n  Send Echo Request to target IP -> receive Echo Reply\n  Measures round-trip time (RTT) and reachability\n  ping 8.8.8.8 -- tests connectivity to Google DNS\n\nTRACEROUTE  (ICMP TTL Exceeded):\n  Sends packets with TTL=1, 2, 3...\n  Each router decrements TTL -> drops at 0 -> sends ICMP TTL Exceeded\n  Builds path map: hop 1 = first router, hop 2 = next router...\n  traceroute 8.8.8.8 reveals entire path to destination\n\nCommon ICMP messages:\n  Type 0  = Echo Reply  |  Type 8  = Echo Request\n  Type 3  = Destination Unreachable  |  Type 11 = TTL Exceeded",
			"fontSize": 15.909222472792147,
			"fontFamily": 5,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "top",
			"containerId": null,
			"originalText": "ICMP rides inside IP packets (Protocol field = 1).\nUsed for diagnostic and control messages -- NOT for user data.\n\nPING  (ICMP Echo Request / Echo Reply):\n  Send Echo Request to target IP -> receive Echo Reply\n  Measures round-trip time (RTT) and reachability\n  ping 8.8.8.8 -- tests connectivity to Google DNS\n\nTRACEROUTE  (ICMP TTL Exceeded):\n  Sends packets with TTL=1, 2, 3...\n  Each router decrements TTL -> drops at 0 -> sends ICMP TTL Exceeded\n  Builds path map: hop 1 = first router, hop 2 = next router...\n  traceroute 8.8.8.8 reveals entire path to destination\n\nCommon ICMP messages:\n  Type 0  = Echo Reply  |  Type 8  = Echo Request\n  Type 3  = Destination Unreachable  |  Type 11 = TTL Exceeded",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.25,
			"hasTextLink": false
		},
